Brazilian football great Zico called on Scolari to quit following the hammering in Belo Horizonte.But Scolari insists he has done a good job with the players he has at his disposal.

'We made the semi-finals, the top four teams in the world,' added Scolari.

'And there were a lot of good teams that were knocked out before us.'

Captain Thiago Silva wants the home fans inside the stadium in Brasilia to get behind their team this weekend.

'This is a bad time so we need strength from our fans,' said the Paris Saint-Germain defender, who returns to the starting XI after sitting out the Germany game through suspension.

'I guarantee that we will play this Saturday's game like it was the final.

'It's almost impossible to explain what happened. This was not the Brazil team we know.'

